I have used your preferred shorthand notation (var:preset|...) and included some example properties to show how each variation can be uniquely styled.
json
{
  "version": 3,
  "styles": {
    "blocks": {
      "core/button": {
        "variations": {
          "fill": {
            "color": { "background": "var:preset|color|primary", "text": "var:preset|color|base" }
          },
          "outline": {
            "border": { "width": "2px", "style": "solid", "color": "var:preset|color|primary" },
            "color": { "background": "transparent", "text": "var:preset|color|primary" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/separator": {
        "variations": {
          "wide": {
            "border": { "width": "4px" },
            "typography": { "fontSize": "2rem" }
          },
          "dots": {
            "color": { "text": "var:preset|color|accent" },
            "typography": { "fontSize": "3rem" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/image": {
        "variations": {
          "rounded": {
            "border": { "radius": "20px" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/quote": {
        "variations": {
          "plain": {
            "border": { "left": { "width": "0px" } },
            "spacing": { "padding": { "left": "0" } }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/site-logo": {
        "variations": {
          "rounded": {
            "border": { "radius": "9999px" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/social-links": {
        "variations": {
          "logos-only": {
            "color": { "background": "transparent" }
          },
          "pill-shape": {
            "border": { "radius": "40px" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/table": {
        "variations": {
          "stripes": {
            "color": { "background": "var:preset|color|base-2" }
          }
        }
      },
      "core/tag-cloud": {
        "variations": {
          "outline": {
            "border": { "width": "1px", "style": "solid" },
            "spacing": { "padding": { "top": "0.25rem", "bottom": "0.25rem", "left": "0.5rem", "right": "0.5rem" } }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
Use code with caution.

Key Implementation Details:
Version 3: Ensures compatibility with the latest features like JSON-based custom variations introduced in WordPress 6.6.
Core Exclusivity: This method works specifically for core-registered style variations; custom styles registered via PHP or JS may require additional setup.
CSS Specificity: Styles defined in variations will automatically target the correct CSS classes (e.g., .is-style-outline or .is-style-rounded). 
